Always use the **quick pull** for UI-only changes, **full deploy** when PHP files or migrations changed.

> `queue:restart` signals the queue workers to gracefully restart after their current job, ensuring they pick up new PHP code. Without it, stale workers run old bytecode until the server reboots.

## Queue Worker — Keep Alive

The queue worker must be running for queued jobs (loyalty, inventory, webhooks) to process.
Payment confirmation SMS now sends **synchronously** (no worker needed), but the worker is still required for other listeners.

**Check if running:**
```bash
ps aux | grep queue:work
```

**Start manually (survives disconnect via nohup):**
```bash
cd /home/bakeandgrill/test.bakeandgrill.mv/backend && nohup php artisan queue:work redis --sleep=3 --tries=3 --max-time=3600 >> storage/logs/queue-worker.log 2>&1 &
```

**Crontab keepalive** (add once via `crontab -e` on the server — auto-restarts if worker dies):
```
* * * * * pgrep -f "queue:work redis" || cd /home/bakeandgrill/test.bakeandgrill.mv/backend && nohup php artisan queue:work redis --sleep=3 --tries=3 --max-time=3600 >> storage/logs/queue-worker.log 2>&1 &
```
